# AssetFlow Domain

These values must remain consistent. Do not create alternative spellings. Do not use lowercase variants. Do not hardcode these strings throughout components. Store and consume them through constants or enums (`src/app/shared/constants/roles.ts`, `statuses.ts`).

## Roles

- `ADMIN`
- `ASSET_MANAGER`
- `DEPARTMENT_HEAD`
- `EMPLOYEE`

## Asset statuses

- `AVAILABLE`
- `ALLOCATED`
- `RESERVED`
- `UNDER_MAINTENANCE`
- `LOST`
- `RETIRED`
- `DISPOSED`

## Allocation/transfer statuses

- `REQUESTED`
- `APPROVED`
- `REJECTED`
- `COMPLETED`
- `RETURNED`
- `OVERDUE`

## Booking statuses

- `UPCOMING`
- `ONGOING`
- `COMPLETED`
- `CANCELLED`

## Maintenance statuses

- `PENDING`
- `APPROVED`
- `REJECTED`
- `TECHNICIAN_ASSIGNED`
- `IN_PROGRESS`
- `RESOLVED`

## Audit verification statuses

- `PENDING`
- `VERIFIED`
- `MISSING`
- `DAMAGED`

## Domain invariants

- Signup always creates an `EMPLOYEE` account.
- Users cannot self-assign elevated roles.
- Asset double-allocation must be prevented.
- Booking overlaps must be rejected.
- Maintenance approval happens before work begins.
- Audit cycles become locked after closing.

These domain requirements come from the AssetFlow specification.
